  "version": 1,
  "updated_at": "2026-02-15",
  "title": {
    "en": "God Renews His Covenant with Abraham"
  },
  "intro": {
    "en": [
      "After the birth of Ishmael, God speaks again to Abraham.",
      "He renews His covenant and gives Abraham a new name that reflects His promise."
    ]
  },
  "blocks": {
    "en": [
      {
        "type": "text",
        "marker": "covenant",
        "icon": "handshake",
        "label": { "en": "A Covenant Promise" },
        "lines": [
          "Some time later God said to him,",
          "“As for me, this is my covenant with you:",
          "You will be the father of many nations.”"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "marker": "new_name",
        "icon": "badge",
        "label": { "en": "A New Name" },
        "lines": [
          "“No longer will you be called Abram;",
          "your name will be Abraham,",
          "for I have made you",
          "a father of many nations.”"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "marker": "fruitfulness",
        "icon": "sprout",
        "label": { "en": "Fruitful and Multiplying" },
        "lines": [
          "“I will make you very fruitful;",
          "I will make nations of you,",
          "and kings will come from you.”"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "marker": "everlasting",
        "icon": "infinity",
        "label": { "en": "An Everlasting Covenant" },
        "lines": [
          "“I will establish my covenant",
          "as an everlasting covenant",
          "between me and you",
          "and your descendants after you",
          "for the generations to come,",
          "to be your God",
          "and the God of your descendants after you.”"
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
  "question": {
    "en": "What do you notice about God’s initiative, the new name, and the promise that continues through generations?"
  },
  "further_reading": {
    "en": ["Genesis 17:1–8"]
  }
}
